label.value: decreased protein processing during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular metabolism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the observed occurrence of protein processing is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein targeting to vacuole

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein targeting to the vacuole is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to nucleus during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is abolished.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal negative regulation of mitotic DNA replication initiation resulting in complete rereplication

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which negative regulation of the initiation of mitotic DNA replication is abnormal, resulting in one or more rounds of rereplication of the entire genome.

definition.value: Consider also annotating to 'abnormal mitosis' (FYPO:0000337), 'inviable swollen elongated cell with enlarged nucleus' (FYPO:0002083), or both. If a cell undergoes several rounds of complete rereplication, the FYPO:0002083 phenotype usually results.

label.value: abnormal negative regulation of mitotic DNA replication initiation resulting in partial rereplication

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which negative regulation of the initiation of mitotic DNA replication is abnormal, resulting in rereplication of part of the genome.

label.value: abnormal negative regulation of mitotic DNA replication initiation resulting in slow rereplication

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which negative regulation of the initiation of mitotic DNA replication is abnormal, resulting in a single round of rereplication of the entire genome, which takes place more slowly than normal replication.

label.value: normal negative regulation of mitotic DNA replication initiation

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which negative regulation of the initiation of mitotic DNA replication is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: swollen elongated cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a cell has a larger volume, greater length, greater diameter, and greater length:diameter ratio than normal.

definition.value: The distinction between this phenotype and centrally constricted (dumbbell-shaped) cells (FYPO:0000779) is that swollen elongated cells do not have a constriction along the long axis. Swollen elongated cells may have a uniform diameter, or may be swollen only around the nucleus.

label.value: abnormal mitotic cell cycle arrest with unreplicated DNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested before cells have replicated genomic DNA, under conditions where arrest does not normally occur.

definition.value: Arrest with unreplicated DNA may occur between mitosis and the beginning of S phase; if only DNA content is measured, the arrest point cannot be determined with greater precision.

label.value: resistance to Dio-9

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of the antibiotic Dio-9 than normal.

label.value: resistance to ethidium bromide

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of ethidium bromide than normal.

label.value: resistance to decamethylenediguanidine

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of decamethylenediguanidine than normal.

label.value: resistance to N,N'-(p-xylylidene)bis-aminoguanidine 2HCl

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of N,N'-(p-xylylidene)bis-aminoguanidine 2HCl than normal.

label.value: normal growth on erythromycin

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing erythromycin.

label.value: normal growth on trichodermin

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing trichodermin.

label.value: normal growth on antimycin A

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing antimycin A.

label.value: normal growth on tetracycline

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing tetracycline.

label.value: normal growth on chloramphenicol

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing chloramphenicol.

label.value: abnormal protein complex localization

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein complex is abnormal.

label.value: decreased SAGA complex localization to promoter region

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of the SAGA complex to chromatin at promoters is decreased.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: abolished transcription during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription does not occur. All genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

label.value: increased cellular trehalose level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of trehalose measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased cellular trehalose level during heat shock

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of trehalose measured in a cell is higher than normal when the cell is subject to heat shock.

label.value: altered cellular trehalose level

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of trehalose measured in a cell differs from normal.

label.value: decreased cellular trehalose level

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of trehalose measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: trehalose absent from cell during heat shock

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of trehalose measured in a cell is too low to detect.

label.value: normal cellular trehalose level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of trehalose measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: resistance to cold

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show decreased sensitivity to cold.

label.value: resistance to freezing

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show decreased sensitivity to freezing.

label.value: resistance to water deprivation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show decreased sensitivity to water deprivation.

label.value: resistance to ethanol

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of ethanol than normal.

label.value: normal growth during cellular response to freezing

value.value: A cell population growth phenotype in which vegetative cells grow normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type) during a cellular response to freezing conditions.

label.value: normal cellular response to water deprivation

value.value: A cellular response phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cellular response to water deprivation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased RNA level during cellular response to endoplasmic reticulum stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to endoplasmic reticulum stress is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: sensitive to tunicamycin

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to tunicamycin. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of tunicamycin that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K14 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 14 of histone H3 occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: increased transcription from CDRE promoter in response to calcium ion

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription from a calcineurin-dependent response element (CDRE)-containing promoter is increased following a calcium ion stimulus.

label.value: normal immediate intracellular calcium spike following extracellular calcium stimulus

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the intracellular calcium ion (Ca2+) concentration briefly increases normally immediately following an extracellular Ca2+ stimulus. Normally, the intracellular Ca2+ concentration increases to a peak in a "burst" within one minute, and then decreases to a new steady-state concentration.

label.value: altered cellular calcium level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of calcium ion measured in a cell differs from normal.

label.value: abnormal immediate intracellular calcium spike following extracellular calcium stimulus

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the intracellular calcium ion (Ca2+) concentration briefly increases abnormally, or does not change, immediately following an extracellular Ca2+ stimulus. Normally, the intracellular Ca2+ concentration increases to a peak in a "burst" within one minute, and then decreases to a new steady-state concentration.

label.value: decreased immediate intracellular calcium spike following extracellular calcium stimulus

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the intracellular calcium ion (Ca2+) concentration briefly increases to a lesser extent than normal immediately following an extracellular Ca2+ stimulus. Normally, the intracellular Ca2+ concentration increases to a peak in a "burst" within one minute, and then decreases to a new steady-state concentration.

label.value: abolished immediate intracellular calcium spike following extracellular calcium stimulus

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the intracellular calcium ion (Ca2+) concentration does not increase immediately following an extracellular Ca2+ stimulus. Normally, the intracellular Ca2+ concentration increases to a peak in a "burst" within one minute, and then decreases to a new steady-state concentration.

label.value: abnormal steady-state intracellular calcium level following extracellular calcium stimulus

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the steady-state intracellular calcium ion (Ca2+) concentration increases abnormally, or does not change, following an extracellular Ca2+ stimulus. Normally, a dose-dependent increased steady-state Ca2+ concentration is reached within 2-3 minutes of extracellular Ca2+ addition, and is sustained for several hours.

label.value: increased steady-state intracellular calcium level following extracellular calcium stimulus

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the steady-state intracellular calcium ion (Ca2+) concentration increases to a greater extent than normal following an extracellular Ca2+ stimulus. Normally, a dose-dependent increased steady-state Ca2+ concentration is reached within 2-3 minutes of extracellular Ca2+ addition, and is sustained for several hours.

label.value: normal growth on tacrolimus

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing tacrolimus.

label.value: normal growth on tacrolimus during salt stress

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing tacrolimus, when the cell is subject to salt stress.

label.value: normal growth on tacrolimus during osmotic stress

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing tacrolimus during a cellular response to osmotic stress.

label.value: resistance to tacrolimus during salt stress

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of tacrolimus than normal when the cells are subject to salt stress.

label.value: abnormal mitotic spindle pole body morphology

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size, shape, or structure of the mitotic spindle pole body is abnormal.

definition.value: Note that an abnormal spindle pole body organization process may, but does not necessarily, result in abnormal spindle pole body structure.
